# NECYPAA XXXVI — Project Rules for Cursor

## Project Overview

Convention website for NECYPAA XXXVI ("Escaping the Mad Realm"). Next.js 15, TypeScript strict, Tailwind CSS, Payload CMS (SQLite), Stripe payments, next-intl (EN/ES), WCAG 2.1 AAA accessibility target.

## Required Reading Before Any Code Change

1. `AA_TRADITIONS_GUARDRAILS.md` — Anonymity rules. No full names, no faces, no promotion. Non-negotiable.
2. `ACCESSIBILITY_GUIDELINES.md` — WCAG 2.1 AAA target. Every component must be keyboard-accessible and screen-reader-friendly.
3. `CONTRIBUTING.md` — Branch naming, commit format, escalation rules.

## Code Conventions

- **TypeScript strict mode** — zero `any` types.
- **Zod validation** on all inputs (`lib/validation.ts`).
- **Rate limiting** on all server actions (`lib/rate-limit.ts`).
- **Tailwind only** — use CSS custom properties from `globals.css` (`var(--nec-purple)`, etc.), never hardcode colors.
- **Radix UI** for complex interactive widgets.
- **Semantic HTML** — `<main>`, `<nav>`, `<section>`, `<article>`, proper ARIA attributes.
- **Accessibility** — every `<img>` needs alt text, every form input needs a label, every interactive element needs keyboard support. Test in all 6 a11y modes.

## Architecture Quick Reference

- **Pages:** `app/[locale]/(frontend)/` — 19 routes with i18n
- **Server actions:** `actions/` — registration, breakfast, free-reg (Stripe + Zod + rate limit)
- **CMS:** Payload at `/admin` — Collections: Users, Events, BlogPosts, FAQ, Media
- **Shared lib:** `lib/` — validation, rate-limit, stripe, types, constants, products
- **Static data:** `lib/data/` — meetings (48KB), states, events
- **Components:** `components/` — sections/, ui/ (shadcn), checkout/, games/, art/

## Testing

- `pnpm test` — 45 Vitest unit tests
- `pnpm test:a11y` — Playwright WCAG accessibility tests
- `pnpm build` — must pass clean before any push

---

## CRITICAL EMERGENCY PROTOCOL — Bus Factor 1

This project is maintained by a solo engineer. The `/.handoff` directory contains living documentation that enables any developer to take over immediately.

**RULE:** Every time you make a structural change, add a dependency, or complete a feature, you MUST autonomously update the relevant files in the `/.handoff` directory. Before formatting a `git push` command, you must update `/.handoff/03_ACTIVE_CONTEXT.md` to reflect the exact state of the pushed code.

**Handoff files:**
- `/.handoff/01_SYSTEM_ARCHITECTURE.md` — Update when: adding integrations, changing database schema, modifying environment variables, altering the tech stack.
- `/.handoff/02_OPERATIONS_AND_DEPLOYMENT.md` — Update when: changing build/deploy steps, adding scripts, modifying CI/CD, changing hosting config.
- `/.handoff/03_ACTIVE_CONTEXT.md` — Update EVERY push: current state, latest changes, known bugs, feature status.

A pre-push git hook enforces this. If you forget, the push will be blocked.
